			<abstract>
				<p>We have designed and fabricated a VLSI synapse that can learn a conditional probability or correlation between spike-based inputs andfeedbacksignals.Thesynapseislowpower,compact,provides nonvolatileweightstorage,andcanperformsimultaneousmultipli-cation and adaptation. We can calibrate arrays of synapses to ensure uniform adaptation characteristics. Finally, adaptation in our synapse does not necessarily depend on the signals used for computation. Consequently, our synapse can implement learning rules thatcorrelatepastandpresentsynapticactivity.Weprovideanaly-sis and experimental chip results demonstrating the operation in learningandcalibrationmode,andshowhowtouseoursynapseto implementvariouslearningrulesinsilicon.</p>
